Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of operations needed to make the given array K-increasing. We can solve this problem using nested loops to iterate through the array and compare each element with the current element (i). If an element is smaller than the current element, swap them. The number of operations needed is incremented. The outer loop iterates from the first element to the (n-k)th element, where n is the size of the array and k is the given parameter. The inner loop iterates from (i+k) to the end of the array. This approach ensures that we only swap elements that need to be swapped, reducing the number of operations needed.

